comments.body: What is the connection between the need for checking for duplicate data and the fact that the labels are stringified?

String representations could conflict with either each other,  if two objects have the same str, or a stringified value could conflict with an existing cat label.  For example,  if categorical labels contained 1 and "1" .

diffHunk:
@@ -1,1 +343,347 @@Stata value labels (pandas categories) must be strings. Column {0} contains
non-string labels which will be converted to strings.  Please check that the
Stata data file created has not lost information due to duplicate labels.
